Epistome subshiny, coarsely, distinctly almost evenly punctured; clypeus relatively more feebly sinuate at middle;
spur of fore tibiae, in males, spatulate and apically hooked. Blackish or piceous black, margins of head and pronotum reddish. Species relatively larger: length 4.5–5.0 mm. Mexico ( Colima , Durango , Hidalgo , Mexico , Oaxaca , Puebla , Veracruz ).......................... .......................................................................................................................
T. glyptus (Bates)
